reviews.review_text: Band on fire to bid Bruce farewell First night in the beautiful Palace, considered the NBA's first "luxury arena."  Do I remember velvet curtains?  Had never seen that in a basketball arena before.  And this two night stand was Hornsby's last as a regular member. They definitely were in the mood to send him off properly.  The first set song selection all fits the theme of a farewell party, and they were SMOKIN', every song.  Candace seemed to have can lights in the ceiling rafters creating running and dancing skeletons in the sky, all in unison; it was the wildest light show I've ever seen.  Whole show is great but this is the hottest first set I ever saw.  And the Dew is monumental. First Gloria since '85 so you know the band thought it was special as well.  Thanks Charlie for this updated version!
